      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsTitle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
            Tales from beyond the Iceclad Ocean&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Errol 
            - 12-12-2000 at 11:26:19</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">Yours truly visited the harsh lands of Velious...</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			I have seen the light! And its blindingly white and hurts yer eyes.... <br><br>As I stepped of the steamdriven gnomish contraption called "Icebreaker", which brought me to the shores of the new land, I was struck by the profound "crispness" of everything around me. It was a far cry from the dusty dry brown Northern Desert of Ro, from whence I came.<br><br>Everything was white. Blindingly white. The air was fresh, untouched by the stench of sprawling cities or cultivated farms. This land was unbroken, wild.<br><br>As I climbed the short way up the hills from the docks, I noticed many feline predators roaming the country-side. Their sleek white fur blending perfectly with the snowy slopes. As I moved away from the well-trodden area surrounding the Icebreaker harbour, my feet started sinking deeper into the deep snow and I called upon Tunare to aid my progress. <br><br>Now, floating a few feet above the ground, I quickly approached a small encampment of igloos huddled together to protect their gnomish inhabitants. The gnomes black leather attire marked them as members of the ill-famed pirates of the Iceclad Ocean, their sharp tongues spitting curses, while they labored to keep their fires burning high.<br><br>It was cold. Never had I felt natures harshness as I did here. And yet, it was beautiful, in an unbridled way. Untouched, unstirred.<br><br>I settled down near a campfire, stretching my hands towards the flames, rubbing them to get the blood flowing again. A gnome pirate eyed me at first, but after realizing his glare had no effect on me, he handed me a small bottle.<br><br>"Drink", he said. And I complied. The strong brew flooded through my veins and brought a flush to my cheeks.<br><br>"Good stuff, eh lubber?", the gnome grinned and I nodded, handing back the flask.<br><br>We sat silently for a while, the only thing stirring was the wind whirling snowflakes into the sizzling fire.<br><br>Then suddenly the gnome leaned forward:<br><br>"First time here, eh?", he glanced at my chain armor and subtle boots. "Not really dressed for the occassion, eh?".<br><br>I nodded. First time here. And it showed...
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
