          <td class="NewsTitle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
            A year in the making....&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Avrohom 
            - 06-12-2000 at 06:44:03</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">First came Soulfire, then Ghoulbane, now... level 50 for Avrohom. And his retirement.</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			In just a few days passed my one year anniversary, I have finally accomplished the three objectives I set out to do last November. It has been only a few minutes now since I acquired level 50 in Karnors Castle, and I am still a little overwhelmed by the fact that I am level 50. So long ago, 30 was an unbelieveable goal. Then 46, plane lvl. Now 50.<br><br> But it has become something of a burden to log in as Avrohom now. His ego, his persona, his character... he became so much bigger than I ever expected him to be. While I cherish all the friends I have made through Avrohom, all the events, quests, adventures, mishaps, and downright disasters... oy vey! There is just not enough time to simply "play" Avrohom.<br><br> Level 50 was the "target level" when I started playing, pre-Kunark period. When Kunark came out, we got post 50 levels and new titles. I prefer to go out as a paladin, not a Cavalier, or knight, or whatever. Avrohom is and will always be a paladin. <br><br> It is my sincere hope that all my friends will join Avi in his last great crusade, to find the ancient dwarven paladin guild of the Icy Ragers in Scars of Velious on December 10th 10 am CST. It is there, in the ancient halls of that most historical paladin guild, that Avi will retire.<br><br> Thanks to everyone who has been a part of Avrohom, you all helped him to be what he is today, for better and for worse. Maybe we will meet again under other names, other personas.<br><br> Gods be with ye!<br><br>/em traces a mystical symbol in the air with his finger<br>/em whispers a prayer to the gods in your name
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
