          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsTitle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
            Do we have what it takes?&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Errol 
            - 02-12-2000 at 16:03:06</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">Avrohom has raised the issue of a lack of dedication when it comes to higher-level events...</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			In a thread on the Private Board, Avrohom is questioning the dedication of our higher levelled characters, when it comes to higher level events or Raids.<br><br>As Event Master Avrohom has been charged with creating and coordinating events. He has done a fantastic job, but something marrs an otherwise exemplary record:<br><br>His high-level raids simply lack backup. No high-levels ever sign up, whether he pre-schedules them well in advance or creates them in the spurr of the moment. <br><br>Now, members have long been advocating for Aegis Lux to sponsor Dragon and Plane raids when we were ready to do so and although Aegis Lux now has the capacity to do so, it seems the focus of our post 40 members has shifted.<br><br>Let me urge everyone in our guild to attend the events we make. This goes for everyone, as I am more than confident that we can handle whatever we set our mind to.<br><br>I am acutely aware that Plane raids or Dragon raids are gonna cost lives and experience, but if that is all its gonna take and no one is willing to pay....<br><br>So, friends. Brother and sisters. Give our Event Master some credit and help him help Aegis Lux move up into the big league.<br><br>I know we can do it!<br><br>Hail Aegis Lux!<br><br>- Errol
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsEnd" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
		  Go make read the threads on the Private Boards concerning these issues...
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
